3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computational geometry, the problem of enumerating cyclic orientations of a graph can be seen as a geometric problem of assigning directions to edges. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses the problem of enumerating all possible cyclic orientations of a graph, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem of finding all possible strategies for assigning directions to edges. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the time and space complexity of the algorithm for enumerating cyclic orientations, which falls under the scope of computational complexity.
